    "text": "A 65-year-old man with chronic kidney disease and pneumonia has a serum potassium concentration of 6.5 mmol/L and a serum creatinine concentration of 200 micromol/L. He is taking ramipril 5 mg once daily and trimethoprim 200 mg twice daily. He complains of having muscle weakness, palpitations, and chest pain.",
